HEADWORD: Zymic
<hw>Zym"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld>
<def>Pertaining to, or produced by, fermentation; -- formerly, by
confusion, used to designate lactic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zymogen</ent>⟦br⟧
